Ivory Coast Budget Minister Denounces BNP Paribas, Citigroup Bank Closures

-- B y   J a s o n   M c L u r e   a n d   O l i v i e r   M o n n i e r
-- 
2011-02-14T13:10:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/ivory-coast-budget-minister-denounces-bnp-paribas-citigroup-bank-closures.html
Justin Kone Katina, the budget
minister of Ivory Coast’s incumbent President Laurent Gbagbo,
denounced the closure of the local branches of  BNP Paribas  and  Citigroup Inc . in the West African nation.  The closure wouldn’t prevent Gbagbo’s administration from
continuing to pay its employees, Katina said in a statement on
state-owned Radio Television Ivoirienne.  Citibank’s office and BICICI, BNP Paribas’ unit, where both
closed when visited today in Abidjan, the commercial capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason McLure in Accra on 
